==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*saiwalō''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[seola|sēola]] (Dutch [[ziel]]), Old High German [[sela|sēla]] (German [[Seele]]), Gothic [[𐍃𐌰𐌹𐍅𐌰𐌻𐌰]].  Further etymology uncertain, though the word corresponds formally with Greek [[αιολος]] ‘quick-moving’.

